<mxfile host="app.diagrams.net" agent="Claude">
  <diagram id="proxy-flow" name="Proxy Flow">
    <mxGraphModel grid="1" page="0" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="950" pageHeight="1900" math="0" shadow="1">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="0" />
        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />
        <mxCell id="s1" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#f8cecc;strokeColor=#b85450;arcSize=4;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="165" width="750" x="75" y="82" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s1n" parent="1" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#b85450;strokeColor=#b85450;fontSize=26;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#ffffff;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;" value="①" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="56" width="56" x="90" y="97" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s1t" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontSize=12;" value="&lt;b&gt;Proxy Startup — Token Acquisition&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;(runs once, before the MCP loop starts)&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;The proxy self-signs an RS256 JWT using the proxy SA private key from &lt;tt&gt;proxy-sa-key.json&lt;/tt&gt;:&lt;br&gt;&lt;tt&gt;iss/sub = proxy-sa@project.iam.gserviceaccount.com &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; aud = https://oauth2.googleapis.com/token&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;tt&gt;POST https://oauth2.googleapis.com/token &amp;nbsp; grant_type=urn:ietf:params:oauth:grant-type:jwt-bearer&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br&gt;Google returns an &lt;b&gt;id_token&lt;/b&gt; (RS256 JWT, ~3600 s, audience = function URL). The proxy caches it&lt;br&gt;and records its expiry timestamp minus 60 seconds for proactive refresh." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="150" width="657" x="158" y="92" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="a12" edge="1" parent="1" source="s1" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;exitX=0.5;exitY=1;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=0.5;entryY=0;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" target="s2">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s2" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;arcSize=4;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="145" width="750" x="75" y="277" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s2n" parent="1" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#6c8ebf;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;fontSize=26;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#ffffff;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;" value="②" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="56" width="56" x="90" y="292" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s2t" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontSize=12;" value="&lt;b&gt;Proxy Startup — Tool Discovery&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;(runs once, immediately after token acquisition)&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;The proxy calls &lt;tt&gt;GET /tools&lt;/tt&gt; with the id_token. Cloud Run validates the OIDC token and returns&lt;br&gt;&lt;tt&gt;TOOL_REGISTRY&lt;/tt&gt; from &lt;tt&gt;main.py&lt;/tt&gt; as a JSON array. Each entry includes &lt;tt&gt;name&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;description&lt;/tt&gt;,&lt;br&gt;&lt;tt&gt;inputSchema&lt;/tt&gt;, and a &lt;tt&gt;route&lt;/tt&gt; field used for dispatch. The proxy builds its route map and strips&lt;br&gt;&lt;tt&gt;route&lt;/tt&gt; before advertising tools to the AI. No tool definitions are hardcoded — add a tool in&lt;br&gt;&lt;tt&gt;main.py&lt;/tt&gt;, redeploy, and the proxy picks it up automatically on next start." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="130" width="657" x="158" y="287" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="a23" edge="1" parent="1" source="s2" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;" target="s3">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s3" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#fff2cc;strokeColor=#d6b656;arcSize=4;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="115" width="750" x="75" y="452" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s3n" parent="1" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#d6b656;strokeColor=#d6b656;fontSize=26;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#ffffff;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;" value="③" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="56" width="56" x="90" y="467" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s3t" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontSize=12;" value="&lt;b&gt;AI Sends a Tool Call&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;Claude Desktop sends a JSON-RPC 2.0 message over stdio to the proxy process:&lt;br&gt;&lt;tt&gt;{&quot;jsonrpc&quot;:&quot;2.0&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:1,&quot;method&quot;:&quot;tools/call&quot;,&quot;params&quot;:{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;list_compute_instances&quot;,&quot;arguments&quot;:{}}}&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br&gt;The proxy reads one newline-delimited JSON message at a time from stdin. Notifications (no id) are silently discarded." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="100" width="657" x="158" y="462" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="a34" edge="1" parent="1" source="s3" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;" target="s4">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s4" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;arcSize=4;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="115" width="750" x="75" y="597" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s4n" parent="1" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#6c8ebf;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;fontSize=26;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#ffffff;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;" value="④" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="56" width="56" x="90" y="612" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s4t" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontSize=12;" value="&lt;b&gt;Route Lookup from Cached Registry&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;The proxy looks up the tool name in the route map built at startup:&lt;br&gt;&lt;tt&gt;list_compute_instances → /resources/compute-instances&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br&gt;If the name is unknown, the proxy writes a JSON-RPC error (−32602) to stdout without making any&lt;br&gt;HTTP request. No network call is made until the route is confirmed." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="100" width="657" x="158" y="607" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="a45" edge="1" parent="1" source="s4" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;" target="s5">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s5" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#fff2cc;strokeColor=#d6b656;arcSize=4;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="130" width="750" x="75" y="742" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s5n" parent="1" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#d6b656;strokeColor=#d6b656;fontSize=26;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#ffffff;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;" value="⑤" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="56" width="56" x="90" y="757" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s5t" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontSize=12;" value="&lt;b&gt;Token Check / Proactive Refresh&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;Before making the HTTP call, the proxy checks if the cached id_token expires within 60 seconds.&lt;br&gt;If so, it re-signs the RS256 JWT and exchanges it for a fresh id_token at &lt;tt&gt;oauth2.googleapis.com&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br&gt;(same flow as step ①). The 60-second buffer prevents a 403 mid-call during long AI sessions.&lt;br&gt;If the token is still valid, this step is a no-op." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="115" width="657" x="158" y="752" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="a56" edge="1" parent="1" source="s5" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;" target="s6">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s6" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#d5e8d4;strokeColor=#82b366;arcSize=4;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="130" width="750" x="75" y="902" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s6n" parent="1" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#82b366;strokeColor=#82b366;fontSize=26;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#ffffff;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;" value="⑥" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="56" width="56" x="90" y="917" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s6t" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontSize=12;" value="&lt;b&gt;Send HTTPS POST to Cloud Function&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;The proxy issues: &lt;tt&gt;POST https://{func-name}-uc.a.run.app/resources/compute-instances&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br&gt;with headers: &lt;tt&gt;Authorization: Bearer &lt;id_token&gt; &amp;nbsp; Content-Type: application/json&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br&gt;Body: &lt;tt&gt;{}&lt;/tt&gt; for parameter-free tools, or &lt;tt&gt;{&quot;label_key&quot;:&quot;env&quot;,&quot;label_value&quot;:&quot;prod&quot;}&lt;/tt&gt; for parameterized tools.&lt;br&gt;The id_token audience must exactly match the Cloud Run service URL — tokens with wrong audience return 403." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="115" width="657" x="158" y="912" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="a67" edge="1" parent="1" source="s6" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;" target="s7">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s7" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#ffe6cc;strokeColor=#d79b00;arcSize=4;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="155" width="750" x="75" y="1062" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s7n" parent="1" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#d79b00;strokeColor=#d79b00;fontSize=26;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#ffffff;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;" value="⑦" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="56" width="56" x="90" y="1077" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s7t" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontSize=12;" value="&lt;b&gt;Cloud Run Validates OIDC Token — Platform Level&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;Cloud Run validates the id_token before the function code runs — no in-code JWT validation needed:&lt;br&gt;RS256 signature verified against Google&apos;s public keys; &lt;tt&gt;aud&lt;/tt&gt; claim must equal the Cloud Run service URL;&lt;br&gt;token must not be expired. Returns &lt;b&gt;403 Forbidden&lt;/b&gt; on any failure — the function never sees&lt;br&gt;unauthenticated requests. Unlike Azure FC1, no JWKS-fetch-and-verify code is needed in &lt;tt&gt;main.py&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;br&gt;Both the CF2 IAM binding and the Cloud Run IAM binding must grant the proxy SA &lt;tt&gt;roles/run.invoker&lt;/tt&gt;." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="140" width="657" x="158" y="1072" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="a78" edge="1" parent="1" source="s7" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;" target="s8">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s8" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#e1d5e7;strokeColor=#9673a6;arcSize=4;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="165" width="750" x="75" y="1247" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s8n" parent="1" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#9673a6;strokeColor=#9673a6;fontSize=26;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#ffffff;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;" value="⑧" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="56" width="56" x="90" y="1262" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s8t" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontSize=12;" value="&lt;b&gt;Handler Queries Cloud Asset Inventory&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;The matched handler executes (e.g. &lt;tt&gt;list_compute_instances&lt;/tt&gt;). &lt;tt&gt;AssetServiceClient&lt;/tt&gt; uses Application&lt;br&gt;Default Credentials — at runtime this resolves to the function SA (&lt;tt&gt;serverless-mcp-func-sa&lt;/tt&gt;), which&lt;br&gt;holds &lt;tt&gt;roles/cloudasset.viewer&lt;/tt&gt; project-wide. No credentials appear in code or environment variables.&lt;br&gt;&lt;tt&gt;list_compute_instances&lt;/tt&gt; uses &lt;tt&gt;ListAssetsRequest&lt;/tt&gt;; label/type/region tools use &lt;tt&gt;SearchAllResourcesRequest&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;tt&gt;list_bucket_objects&lt;/tt&gt; uses &lt;tt&gt;google.cloud.storage.Client&lt;/tt&gt; (ADC, &lt;tt&gt;roles/storage.objectViewer&lt;/tt&gt;).&lt;br&gt;Results are formatted as plain text — no raw proto structs returned to the AI." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="150" width="657" x="158" y="1257" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="a89" edge="1" parent="1" source="s8" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;" target="s9">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s9" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#d5e8d4;strokeColor=#82b366;arcSize=4;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="135" width="750" x="75" y="1442" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s9n" parent="1" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#82b366;strokeColor=#82b366;fontSize=26;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#ffffff;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;" value="⑨" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="56" width="56" x="90" y="1457" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="s9t" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontSize=12;" value="&lt;b&gt;Result Returns to the AI&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;The plain-text response body travels back through Cloud Run to the proxy. The proxy wraps it&lt;br&gt;as an MCP content block and writes the JSON-RPC response to stdout:&lt;br&gt;&lt;tt&gt;{&quot;jsonrpc&quot;:&quot;2.0&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:1,&quot;result&quot;:{&quot;content&quot;:[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Compute Engine instances (2 total)...&quot;}]}}&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br&gt;Claude Desktop reads the response, and Claude narrates the result directly to the user.&lt;br&gt;The Cloud Function backend is completely transparent — the AI sees only a local MCP tool call." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="120" width="657" x="158" y="1452" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
</mxfile>
